To enhance performance, one could consider adjusting the ratio to allow for more nuanced feature recalibration. A lower ratio would compress the channels more, potentially capturing higher-level features but at the risk of losing some fine details. Conversely, a higher ratio reduces compression, allowing for more precise control over each channel but possibly increasing computational overhead.

